## 1. Hero Section Experiments

**Headline tests:**
- Outcome-focused vs. feature-focused headline
- Short headline (under 8 words) vs. long headline (with subheadline)
- Question headline vs. statement headline
- Headline with a specific number/stat vs. without
- Customer-centric ("You") vs. product-centric ("We/Our")

**Visual tests:**
- Product screenshot/demo vs. lifestyle image vs. illustration
- Video hero vs. static image
- Background image vs. solid color background
- Hero with a person's face vs. abstract visual
- Animated/interactive hero vs. static

**Layout tests:**
- Left-aligned text with right image vs. centered text
- Hero with form embedded vs. hero with CTA button only
- Full-viewport hero vs. shorter hero showing content below
- Single CTA hero vs. hero with primary and secondary CTA

---

## 2. CTA Experiments

**Button copy tests:**
- Action verb ("Start") vs. benefit verb ("Get")
- With urgency ("Start Free Trial Today") vs. without ("Start Free Trial")
- First person ("Start My Trial") vs. second person ("Start Your Trial")
- Specific ("Get 14-Day Free Trial") vs. general ("Try It Free")
- With risk reducer ("Start Free, No Credit Card") vs. without

**Button design tests:**
- High-contrast color vs. muted color
- Large button vs. standard button
- Button with icon/arrow vs. text only
- Rounded vs. sharp corners
- With supporting microcopy below the button vs. without

**Placement tests:**
- Sticky/floating CTA bar vs. standard placement
- CTA frequency: every section vs. every other section
- CTA at end of testimonial section vs. end of feature section
- Exit-intent CTA vs. no exit-intent

---

## 3. Social Proof Experiments

**Type tests:**
- Customer logos vs. testimonial quotes vs. review scores
- Video testimonials vs. text testimonials
- Case study snippets with metrics vs. general praise quotes
- Real-time activity feed ("X people signed up today") vs. static count
- Industry-specific testimonials vs. general

**Format tests:**
- Carousel testimonials vs. static grid
- Named and attributed quotes vs. anonymous
- Testimonials with photos vs. without
- Long detailed testimonials vs. short one-liners
- Star ratings display vs. written reviews

**Placement tests:**
- Social proof above the fold vs. below the fold
- Trust badges near the CTA vs. in footer
- Testimonials before pricing vs. after pricing
- Logos bar at top of page vs. mid-page

